The Arrival is a 1996 science fiction film directed by David Twohy and starring Charlie Sheen, and co-starring Lindsay Crouse, Richard Schiff, Ron Silver, and Teri Polo. Sheen stars as radio astronomer Zane Zaminsky who discovers evidence of intelligent alien life and quickly gets thrown into the middle of a conspiracy that turns his life upside down. The film is now considered a cult classic.A Blu-ray version of the film was released April 21, 2009. A sequel, Arrival II: The Second Arrival was released on November 6, 1998.
